first initalise:
git config --global user.name "yourname"

git config --global user.email "youremail.com"

use pwd to see where you are

user cd to move

create a new folder - mkdir folderName

move into the folder and initalise git using - git init

set up a link to the git folder :
git remote add *NAME* http//www.file address
eg
git remote add origion https://github.com/emjheneghan/Test.git

to paste the link, right click on the top of the git bash screen,
choose edit, then paste

check that you added a name - git remote, 
the result should list any shortcuts you made, aka, origin

to pull from git - git pull http/www.webaddress

to push to git
1. add your change to an intermediate layer, git add .
2. commit your change and add a comment, git commit -m"this is a comment"
3. you can check the status, git status - to see if your commit worked
4. push, git push origin master, origin the nickname, master is you

